OL,3,CInside Portugal's groundbreaking
OL,4,Cwildfire prevention strategy
OL,6,FIn June of that year, 66 people were
OL,7,Fkilled, some of them burnt alive in
OL,8,Ftheir cars, after four deadly
OL,9,Fwildfires erupted within minutes of
OL,10,Feach other in central Portugal.
OL,12,FIt devastated an area four times the
OL,13,Fsize of Lisbon, destroyed hundreds of
OL,14,Fhomes and redefined the country's
OL,15,Fapproach to firefighting and
OL,16,Fsuppression.
OL,18,FWe have come to these mountains to try
OL,19,Fto find one of the newest weapons
OL,20,Fbeing deployed here against the threat
OL,21,Fof fire.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
